  <title>Quantifying Need</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Courses that use OER should generally review and revise their OER content every four years.
      In some rapidly evolving disciplines or disciplines that rely on recent data, this should
      happen more frequently. This process takes time and labor. Here, we attempt to quantify the
      necessary labor to maintain OERs at PCC this way.
    </p>
  </introduction>
